By using the `isValidType` function as a type guard, you can tell the TypeScript compiler that you know the value of `myValue` will only be of type `ValidType` in practice, even though it has a type of `any` in theory. This allows you to narrow the type of `myValue` to `ValidType` without having to explicitly specify the type in the code.

